You get the value in DMS (Degrees Minutes Seconds) so you will need to convert to something more useful like DD (Decimal Degrees). [Geographic coordinate conversion](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Geographic_coordinate_conversion)
Here's the function I use to convert: 
```js
function ConvertDMSToDD (degrees, minutes, seconds, direction) {
  if (typeof degrees !== 'number'
    || typeof minutes !== 'number'
    || typeof seconds !== 'number') return undefined;
  const dd = degrees
    + minutes / 60
    + seconds / (60 * 60);
  if (direction === 'S' || direction === 'W') {
    return dd * -1;
  } // Don't do anything for N or E
  return dd;
}
```

